    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-09T12:48:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-09T12:48:00-05:00" n="113"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d113">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.1511/68: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Belt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-09T12:00:00-05:48">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 9, 1918, noon.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 7.40 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s January 29, 8 p.m. Minister for Foreign Affairs yesterday formally
                    notified Legation appointment of Dr. Policarpo Bonilla, Envoy Extraordinary and
                    Minister Plenipotentiary on Special Mission, United States, leaving Honduras in
                    March. Legation to be informed later date expected departure.</p>
                <p>He is considered the most intelligent Honduranean here with considerable
                    influence politically. He was formerly President and has visited Washington
                    before on special mission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Belt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
